Are there any MUST READ books on programming?
I'm thinking of books that are more generic than "How to learn X (language) the hard way", or "you don't know Javascript" or anything to that effect.
But books that address paradigmes, approaches, and software development at large?

<@U6MLHLP29> hate to make you responsible for this one, but you know we're onto you :eyes: :books: :smile:

I should note I just found a few on my to-read list, but I don't know where I have them from or how good they are:
• Clean Code: A Handbook of Agile Software Craftsmanship
• Clean Architecture: A Craftsman’s Guide to Software Structure and Design
• The Clean Coder: A Code of Conduct for Professional Programmers
• Practical Object Oriented Design
• 99 Bottles of OOP - 2nd Edition
• Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software
